4d43fdc0-3b68-45a2-b6c2-c33821bb7fd5	0a51428e-cad6-473f-bc0a-857f13ddebec	en	The Tale of Friendly Animals	There was a group of friendly animals in the forest, living together in peace and harmony. There was the wise elephant, the swift wolf, the playful monkey, and the brave cheetah. They would play together and enjoy their time, but one day they found a small injured bird. They helped the bird until it recovered, and it thanked them for their help. They realized that teamwork and mutual help are the key to true happiness. From that day on, they became even more united and friendly, keeping the spirit of sportsmanship and cooperation in everything they did.	The friendly animals in the forest learned that teamwork and mutual help are the key to true happiness. They realized that cooperation and sportsmanship can change everything.	\N
